<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-05-0660 </DOCNO><TEXT>Part 1 of this book deals with the basic physics of nuclear medicine includingdosimetry, radiation exposure of patients and personnel, and radiationprotection. Part 2 deals with the radionuclides and radiopharmaceuticalsused in nuclear medicine. In part 2 the measuring and evaluation equipmentis discussed and part 4 is concerned with the principles of measurement.How nuclear diagnostics for the different organs work in practice isdescribed in part 5. Part 6 is dedicated to therapy.</TEXT></DOC>